	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why does everybody insist on making their own sound engine. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>
<br />I can't speak for everyone else, but for me that's an opportunity to learn even more about the NES. I want to master everything about it, and that includes sound. Also, I hate using other people's code in my projects. You can call me a control freak, but I like to know exactly what happens in every part of my programs.
<br />
<br />About ShootNES, looks cool so far. I'm interested to see where it goes.

		

		</td>
